  "narrative": "As of April 2, 2026, capital is flowing predominantly into the Energy sector, which has seen a significant increase of 8.7% compared to the SPY, indicating strong investor confidence in energy stocks. This is likely driven by a combination of favorable macroeconomic conditions, including a lower fed funds rate of 3.64%, which is down 16% year-over-year, making borrowing cheaper and potentially boosting energy investments. Additionally, the Technology and Utilities sectors have also attracted capital, with increases of 2.5% and 2.4%, respectively, suggesting a broader interest in stable growth sectors amidst a volatile market, as indicated by the VIX at 24.06, up 12% YoY.\n\nInvestors should keep an eye on the bearish options positions in IWM, LLY, SPY, and TMO, which may signal caution in small-cap stocks and certain large-cap companies. Conversely, the bullish sentiment surrounding AAPL, AMZN, BLK, BRK-B, and DVN could indicate a shift towards growth and value stocks, particularly in technology and energy. Monitoring these trends and the performance of these sectors will be crucial in understanding future capital flows.",
